  "text": "Drinking activity of intact females showed estrous cycledependent changes (Fig. 2B, E) . Changes of activity rhythms caused by estrous cycle have been previously reported in various rodent species [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In this study, some mice showed clear estrous cycle-dependent changes (5 of 7 and 4 of 7 in WT and AhRKO, respectively). Of those that showed cyclicity, WT females had a cycle of 3 to 4 days whereas AhRKO had longer cycles of about 5 to 6 days. However, the circadian period under DD and LL was not significantly different between intact WT and AhRKO females (Fig. 2H) .",
